00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:04,150
I done wrestled with him.
You can't tell me nothing about death.

236
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:07,517
Death ain't nothing
but a fastball on the outside corner,

237
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:11,435
and you know what I do with that.
Look here, Bono, am I lying?

238
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:14,354
You get one of them fastballs
about waist high

239
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:16,033
on the outside corner of the plate

240
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,839
where you can get
the meat of the bat on it,

241
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:21,152
and, good God, you could kiss it good-bye.

242
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,197
- Am I lying?
- No, you telling the truth.

243
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,794
I seen you do it.

244
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:30,000
If I'm lying, that's 450 feet worth of lying.
That's all death is to me.

245
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:32,515
A fastball on the outside corner.

246
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,910
I don't know why you want to
get on talking about death?

247
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,320
Ain't nothing wrong
with talking about death.

248
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,119
That's a part of life!
Everybody gonna die.

249
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,515
You gonna die. I'm gonna die.

250
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,398
Bono gonna die. Hell, we all gonna die.

251
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,836
But you ain't got to talk about it.
I don't like talking about it.

252
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:45,115
Well, you the one brought it up.

253
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,759
Me and Bono talking about baseball.

254
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,797
You come telling me
I'm gonna drink myself to death.

255
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:50,155
Ain't that right, Bono?

256
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:52,471
Now you know I drink just
but one night out the week,

257
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:53,710
that's Friday night.

258
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,513
I drink just enough to where
I can handle it.

259
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,114
Then I leaves it alone. I cuts it loose.

260
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,237
So, you ain't got to worry
about me drinking myself to death

261
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,919
'cause I ain't worrying about death.

262
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,674
I done seen him, done wrestled with him.

263
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:05,035
Look here, Bono.

264
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:08,272
I look up one day,
and Death is marching straight at me,

265
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:10,477
like soldiers on parade.

266
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:12,916
The Army of Death
was marching straight at me.

267
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,357
It was the middle of July, 1941.

268
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,671
And it got real cold, just like it be winter.

269
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:20,353
And it seemed like Death, himself,

270
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:22,477
reached out
and touched me on the shoulder.

271
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:25,837
He touched me like I touch you now.
I got cold as ice.

272
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,195
Death standing there, grinning at me.

273
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:28,999
Troy, why don't you hush that talk.

274
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:32,357
I said, "What you want, Mr. Death?
You be wanting me?

275
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,318
"You done sent your army
to be getting me?"

276
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,356
I looked him dead in the eye.

277
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:36,510
I wasn't fearing nothing.

278
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:39,274
I was ready to tangle,
just like I'm ready to tangle now!

279
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,518
Bible says be ever vigilant.

280
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,910
So, I don't get but so drunk.
I got to keep watch.

281
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,593
Troy was right down there
at Mercy Hospital.

282
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,034
You remember he had that pneumonia,

283
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:49,032
laying there with a fever,
talking plumb out his head.

284
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,395
And Death standing there, staring at me,

285
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:51,920
carrying that sickle in his hand.

286
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:57,758
Finally, he say, "You want to be
bound over for another year?"

287
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:59,991
Just like that. He say,

288
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:03,869
"You want to be bound over
for another year?"

289
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:07,954
I said, "Bound over, hell!
We can settle this right now."

290
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:11,471
He kinda fell back when I said that.
And all the cold went out of me.

291
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:13,552
I reached down, I grabbed that sickle.

292
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,433
I threw it as far as I could throw it,

293
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:17,193
and me and him commenced to wrestling.

294
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:20,796
We wrestled for... Carry the six...
Three days and three nights!

295
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:23,190
Now, I don't know
where I got the strength from,

296
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:24,999
'cause every time
he tried to get the best of me,

297
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:29,199
I reached way deep down inside myself,
found the strength to do him one better.

298
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:30,873
Every time Troy tells that story,

299
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,189
he find different ways to tell it,

300
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:33,760
different things to make up.

301
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:35,240
I ain't making up nothing, woman.

302
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:36,879
I'm telling you
the facts of what happened.

303
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:39,236
I wrestled with Death
for three days and three nights,

304
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:41,795
and I'm standing here
to tell you about it.

305
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:46,157
All right. At the end of the third night,

306
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:49,312
we done weakened each other
to where we can't even hardly move.

307
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,390
Death stood up.

308
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:52,676
He threw on that robe,
had a white robe with a hood on it.

309
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:56,077
He throwed on that robe
and went off to look for that sickle.

310
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:59,836
He said, "I'll be back."
Just like that. "I'll be back."

311
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:03,038
I said, "Yeah?
Well, you gonna have to find me!"

312
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,236
I wasn't no fool.

313
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,120
I wasn't going looking for him.

314
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:08,760
I know Death ain't nothing to play with.
And I know he's gonna get me.

315
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:11,878
I know I got to join his army,
his camp followers.

316
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:14,839
But as long as I keep up my strength
and see him coming,

317
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:18,800
as long as I keep up my vigilance,
he gonna have to fight to get me.

318
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:20,155
I ain't going easy.

319
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:24,236
Well, look here,
since you got to keep up your vigilance,

320
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,754
let me have the bottle.

321
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:27,752
Hell, I shouldn't have told you that part.

322
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,956
I should have left out that part.

323
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,520
Troy be talking all that stuff.

324
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,956
Half the time, he don't even know
what he be talking about!

325
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,037
- Yeah, Bono know me better than that.
- That's right, I know you.

326
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:38,318
I know you got some
Uncle Remus in your blood.

327
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,676
You got more stories
than the devil got sinners.

328
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:43,355
Hell, I done seen him, too.
Done talked to the devil.

329
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,079
Nobody wants to be hearing that stuff!

330
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,155
Hey, Pop.

331
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,754
What you come "Hey, Poppin'" me for?

332
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:52,911
How you doing, Rose?

333
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,515
Mr. Bono, how you doing?

334
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:57,273
Hey, Lyons, how you been?

335
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:58,794
He must've been doing all right.

336
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,030
I ain't seen him around here last week.

337
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:01,759
Troy, leave your boy alone.
He come by to see you

338
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:03,354
and you want to start all that nonsense.

339
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,760
I ain't bothering Lyons.
Here, get you a drink.

340
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:06,320
Me and him got an understanding.

341
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:09,552
I know why he come by to see me,
and he know I know.

342
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,518
Come on, Pop. I just stopped by to say hi,

343
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:12,670
see how you was doing.

344
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,752
- You ain't stopped by yesterday.
- You staying for supper, Lyons?

345
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:16,069
I got some chicken cooking in the oven.

346
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:17,958
No, Rose, thanks.
I just was in the neighborhood

347
00:14:18,040 --> 00:14:19,440
and thought I'd stop by for a minute.

348
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:21,000
Yeah, you was
in the neighborhood all right.

349
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,355
Nigger, you telling the truth there.

350
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:24,193
You was in the neighborhood
'cause it's my payday.

351
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,511
Well, hell, since you mentioned it,
let me have $10.

352
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:30,358
I'll be damned. I'll die and go to hell

353
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:32,909
and play blackjack with the devil
before I give you $10.

354
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,879
That's what I want to know about,
that devil you done seen.

355
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:38,111
Pop done seen the devil?
You too much, Pop.

356
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:40,431
- Yeah, I done seen him.
- He ain't seen no devil.

357
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:42,637
I told him that man
ain't had nothing to do with the devil.

358
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,791
Anything he can't understand,
he want to call it the devil.

359
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:48,078
Look here, Bono. I go by Hertzberger's
to get some furniture.

360
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:50,959
You got three rooms for $298.
That what it say on the radio.

361
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:54,397
"Three rooms, $298."
He made up a little song about it.

362
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:57,473
I get down there,
man tell me I can't get no credit.

363
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,791
I'm working every day,
can't get no credit.

364
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:00,996
What to do?

365
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:02,793
I got an empty house
with some raggedy furniture.

366
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:04,036
Cory ain't got no bed.

367
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:06,237
He's sleeping on a pile of rags
on the floor.

368
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:08,357
Working every day, can't get no credit.

369
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,840
I come back here, Rose'll tell you,

370
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:11,798
madder than hell,
trying to figure out what to do.

371
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:13,236
Come a knock on the door.

372
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:15,357
I ain't been living but three days,
who know I'm here?

373
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:17,597
I open the door. Devil standing there.

374
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:18,716
Bigger than life.

375
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,678
White fella,
got on good clothes and everything.

376
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:21,910
Standing there
with a clipboard in his hand.

377
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,275
Now, I ain't got to say nothing.

378
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:24,834
First words come out of his mouth,

379
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:27,754
"I understand you need some furniture
and can't get no credit."

380
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:31,311
I liked to fell over. He said,
"I'll give you all the credit you want,

381
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:33,392
"but you gonna have to pay
the interest on it."

382
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:34,914
Now, I told him,
he give me them three rooms,

383
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,480
he can charge whatever he want.

384
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,199
Next day, a truck pull up here,

385
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:39,919
two men unload them three rooms.

386
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:42,236
Man what drove the truck give me a book.

387
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:45,757
Said first of the month,
send $10 to the address in the book,

388
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:46,950
everything'll be fine.

389
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:48,520
Said if you miss a payment,

390
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,274
the devil was coming back,
and there'll be hell to pay.

391
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,874
That was 15 years ago.

392
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:56,476
To this day, first day of every month,
I send my $10,

393
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:57,954
just like clockwork. Rose'll tell you.

394
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:00,874
- Troy lying.
- I ain't never seen that man since.

395
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,838
Now, you tell me,
who else that gonna be but the devil?

396
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:04,991
And I ain't sold my soul
or nothing like that.

397
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:07,800
No, I wouldn't have truck with the devil
over nothing like that.

398
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:11,476
But I got my furniture.
And I send my $10, just like clockwork.

399
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:14,439
How long you say
you been paying this $10 a month?

400
00:16:14,520 --> 00:16:15,556
15 years.

401
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:19,316
Hell, ain't you finished paying for it yet?
How much the man done charge you?

402
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:22,632
Hell, I done paid for it.
I done paid for it 10 times over.

403
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:23,995
Fact is, I'm scared to stop paying.

404
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:26,515
Troy lying.
We got that furniture from Mr. Glickman.

405
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,319
He ain't paying no $10 a month to nobody.

406
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,676
Hell, woman,
Bono know I ain't that big a fool.

407
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:33,315
I was just getting ready to say,
I know where there's a bridge for sale.

408
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,470
I'll tell you this.

409
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:36,313
It don't matter to me if it was the devil.

410
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,754
It don't matter if the devil give credit.

411
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:39,752
- Somebody got to give it.
- It ought to matter.

412
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:42,116
You walking around here saying
you gonna make truck with the devil,

413
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,634
God's the one
you're gonna have to answer to.

414
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,234
He's the one gonna be at the Judgment.

415
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:47,232
Yeah, well, look here, Pop,
let me have that $10.

416
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,476
I'll give it back to you.

417
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:49,994
Bonnie got a job working at the hospital.

418
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:51,150
Bono, what did I tell you?

419
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:52,839
Only time I see this nigger
is when he want something.

420
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,070
That's the only time I see him.

421
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:56,710
Come on, Pop,
Mr. Bono don't want to hear all that.

422
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,996
Let me have the $10.
I told you, Bonnie's working!

423
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,435
What that mean to me if Bonnie's working?

424
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:03,672
I don't care if she working.
Go ask her for $10 if she's working.

425
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:06,434
Talking about Bonnie working.
Why ain't you working?

426
00:17:06,840 --> 00:17:08,877
Pop, you know I can't find no decent job.

427
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:10,917
Where am I gonna get a job at?
You know I can't get no job.

428
00:17:11,120 --> 00:17:13,316
I told you, I know some people down there.

429
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,232
I can get you on the rubbish
if you want to work.

430
00:17:15,320 --> 00:17:18,119
I told you that last time you
come back here asking for something.

431
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,475
No, Pop, thanks, that ain't for me.

432
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:21,080
I don't want to be carrying
nobody's rubbish.

433
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,992
I don't want to be punching
nobody's time clock.

434
00:17:23,080 --> 00:17:25,072
What's the matter?
You too good to carry people's rubbish?

435
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:27,038
Where you think that $10
you talking about comes from?

436
00:17:27,120 --> 00:17:28,873
I'm just supposed to haul people's rubbish

437
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:30,838
and give my money to you
'cause you too lazy to work?

438
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:32,036
You're too lazy to work

439
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:33,713
and want to know
why you ain't got what I got.

440
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,439
What hospital Bonnie working at, Mercy?

441
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:37,273
She down at Passavant,
working in the laundry.

442
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:39,192
I ain't got nothing as it is. I give you $10,

443
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:40,634
I got to eat beans the rest of the week?

444
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:42,120
No, you ain't getting no $10 over here.

445
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:43,720
You ain't got to be eating no beans.

446
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:45,075
I don't know why you want to say that?

447
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,992
I ain't got no extra money!

448
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,030
Gabe done moved out,

449
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:52,476
giving his money over there
to Miss Pearl, paying her rent.

450
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:53,755
Things done got tight around here.

451
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,320
I can't afford to be
giving you every payday.

452
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:58,040
I ain't asked you to give me nothing.
I asked you to loan me $10.

453
00:17:58,120 --> 00:17:59,190
I know you got $10.

454
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,397
Yeah, I got it. You know why I got it?

455
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:03,756
'Cause I don't throw my money away
on them streets.

456
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:05,877
You want to live the fast life,
being a musician,

457
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,599
running around in them clubs and things,

458
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,114
then learn to take care of yourself.

459
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:12,352
You ain't gone find me asking
nobody for nothing!

460
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:13,760
I spent too many years without.

461
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:15,274
Hey, you and me is two different people.

462
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:18,592
I done learned my mistake
and I learned to do what's right by it.

463
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,353
You still trying to get
something for nothing.

464
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:21,590
Life don't owe you nothing.

465
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:24,275
You owe it to yourself.
Ask Bono. He'll tell you I'm right.

466
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:26,795
You got your way of
dealing with the world, I got mine.

467
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:28,678
Only thing that matters to me
is the music.

468
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:31,111
Yeah, I can see that.
Don't matter how you gonna eat,

469
