You been running out of here
every Saturday for weeks.

738
00:31:44,200 --> 00:31:47,034
I thought you were gonna
work on this fence.

739
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:49,351
I'm gonna go down to Taylors' and...

740
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:39,870
Mama?

741
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:44,120
Cory. Your daddy
like to have a fit with you

742
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:47,079
running out of here this morning
without doing your chores.

743
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:48,435
You all right?

744
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:51,797
He say you supposed to be
helping him with the fence.

745
00:32:51,880 --> 00:32:53,280
I told you I had to go to practice.

746
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:55,352
And he's been saying that
the last four or five Saturdays,

747
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:58,512
and then don't ever do nothing
but go down to Taylors'.

748
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:02,031
- You told him about the recruiter?
- Yeah, I told him.

749
00:33:02,120 --> 00:33:04,760
- Well, what'd he say?
- He didn't say nothing too much.

750
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:07,480
Go on and get started on your chores
before he gets back here.

751
00:33:07,560 --> 00:33:10,200
Go on and scrub down them steps

752
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:13,159
before he come back here hollering
and carrying on!

753
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:15,072
Go! Boy, go!

754
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:40,991
Go on, Troy.
You liked to scare me to death.

755
00:33:41,120 --> 00:33:42,270
What was the score of the game?

756
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:44,192
Lucille had me on the phone.
I couldn't keep up with it.

757
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:45,794
What do I care about the game?
Come here, woman.

758
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:47,030
I thought you went down to Taylors'

759
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:48,873
to listen to the game. Go on, Troy.

760
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,679
I thought you're supposed to
be putting up the fence.

761
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:53,116
I'll put it up when I finish with what...

762
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:55,556
Is at hand.

763
00:33:55,640 --> 00:33:57,711
Go on, Troy. I ain't studying you!

764
00:33:57,800 --> 00:34:00,713
I'm studying you.
I'm finna do my homework.

765
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:02,473
Troy, you better leave me alone!

766
00:34:05,120 --> 00:34:06,713
Where Cory?
That boy brought his butt home yet?

767
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:08,200
He's upstairs doing his chores.

768
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:09,600
Cory, get your butt...

769
00:34:11,080 --> 00:34:13,276
- Where you going?
- I'll be right back.

770
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:15,955
- When?
- I'm just going right down the street.

771
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:19,791
Where? Who?

772
00:34:22,640 --> 00:34:24,313
Troy, go in the house!

773
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:54,398
You just now coming here
from leaving this morning?

774
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:55,755
- Yeah, I had to go to football practice...
- Yeah, what?

775
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:56,830
Yes, sir.

776
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:58,400
I ain't but two seconds off you, no way.

777
00:34:58,480 --> 00:35:00,153
That garbage
sitting in there, overflowing.

778
00:35:00,240 --> 00:35:01,515
You ain't done none of your chores.

779
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:02,795
Now you come in here,
talking about, "Yeah."

780
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:04,314
I was just getting ready
to do my chores now, Pop.

781
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,631
Your first chore is to help me
with this fence on Saturday.

782
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:08,279
Everything else come after that.

783
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:10,670
Now, get that saw,
we gonna cut these boards.

784
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:17,791
Hey, Pop. Why don't you buy a TV?

785
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:20,315
What I want with a TV?
What I want one of them for?

786
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:23,199
Everybody got one. Earl, Ba Bra, Jesse.

787
00:35:23,680 --> 00:35:25,478
I ain't asked who had one,
I said what I want with one?

788
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:28,035
So, you can watch it.
They got lots of things on TV.

789
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:29,349
- Baseball and everything.
- Yeah?

790
00:35:29,480 --> 00:35:30,755
We could watch the World Series.

791
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:32,797
- Yeah, how much this TV cost?
- I don't know.

792
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:35,475
They got 'em on sale for about $200.

793
00:35:35,560 --> 00:35:37,199
- $200?
- That ain't that much, Pop.

794
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:39,870
No, that's just $200.

795
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:43,071
You see that roof you got
sitting over your head at night?

796
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:45,272
Let me tell you something about that roof.

797
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:49,240
It's been 10 years
since that roof was last tarred.

798
00:35:49,320 --> 00:35:52,438
See, now snow come this winter,
sit up on that roof like it is,

799
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:54,477
it's gonna seep inside,
just gonna be a little bit,

800
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:56,876
you ain't gonna hardly notice it,
then next thing you know,

801
00:35:56,960 --> 00:35:58,440
it's gonna be leaking all over the house.

802
00:35:58,520 --> 00:36:02,480
Then the wood rot from all that water,
and you gonna need a whole new roof.

803
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:04,756
Now how much you think it cost
to get that roof fixed?

804
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:09,080
- I don't know.
- $264 cash money. See?

805
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:10,879
While you be thinking about a TV,

806
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:15,113
I got to be thinking about the roof
or whatever else go wrong around here.

807
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:17,112
Now if you had $200, what would you do?

808
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:19,590
Fix the roof, or buy a TV?

809
00:36:19,680 --> 00:36:22,070
I'd buy a TV.
And when the roof started to leak,

810
00:36:22,200 --> 00:36:23,475
if it needed fixing, I'd fix it.

811
00:36:23,560 --> 00:36:24,914
Where you gonna get your money from?

812
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,320
You done spent it on a TV.

813
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:29,791
You gonna sit up in there, let that
water run all over your brand-new TV?

814
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:31,439
Pop, you got the money. I know you do.

815
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:33,239
- Where I got it at?
- In the bank.

816
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:34,595
You want to see my bank book?

817
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:37,479
You want to see that $73.22
I got sitting up in there?

818
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:39,233
You don't have to pay for it
all at one time.

819
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:41,198
You can put a down payment on it,
and carry it on with you.

820
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:43,954
Not me. I ain't owing nobody nothing
if I can help it.

821
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:46,600
Miss a payment, they come
and snatch it right out of your house.

822
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:49,718
Then what you got? See?

823
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:53,316
Now, when I get $200 clear,
I'll buy me a TV.

824
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:56,797
Right now, when I get $264,
I'm gonna get that roof fixed.

825
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:57,870
Pop...

826
00:36:57,960 --> 00:37:00,680
You go get you $200
and buy you a TV if you want to.

827
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:02,353
I got better things to do with my money.

828
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:04,671
I can't get $200. I ain't never seen $200.

829
00:37:05,080 --> 00:37:06,309
All right, I'll tell you what.

830
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:09,598
You get $100,
I'll put the other $100 with it.

831
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:11,160
All right, I'm gonna show you.

832
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:14,472
Yeah, show me how you can
cut these boards right now.

833
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:17,635
There you go. That's $200 worth.

834
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,153
- The Pirates won today.
- Yeah?

835
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:23,356
That makes five in a row.

836
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:25,875
I ain't thinking about no Pirates.
They got an all-white team.

837
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:29,636
Got that boy, though,
that Puerto Rican boy, Clemente?

838
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,030
Don't even half play him.

839
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:33,112
That boy could be something
if they'd give him a chance.

840
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:35,238
Play him one day,
sit him on the bench the next.

841
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:36,549
He gets lots of chances to play.

842
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:38,552
I'm talking about playing every day,
playing regular,

843
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:40,199
so you can get your timing,
that's what I'm talking about.

844
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:42,391
They got some white guys on the team
that don't play every day.

845
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:43,709
You can't play everybody at the same time.

846
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:45,598
If they got a white fellow
sitting on the bench,

847
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:48,320
you can bet your last dollar
he can't play.

848
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:50,437
Colored guy got to be twice as good
to get on the team.

849
00:37:50,520 --> 00:37:53,319
That's why I don't want you
getting all tied up in them sports.

850
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:55,437
Man on the team, what it get him?

851
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:57,477
Got colored on the team,
don't even use him.

852
00:37:57,560 --> 00:38:00,314
Same as not having them.
All them teams the same.

853
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:02,676
The Braves got Hank Aaron
and Wes Covington.

854
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:04,792
Hank Aaron hit two home runs today.
