855
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:06,837
Aaron ain't nobody.
That's what you supposed to do.

856
00:38:06,920 --> 00:38:08,718
That's how the game's supposed
to be played.

857
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:11,520
Ain't nothing to it. It's a matter of getting
your timing and follow through.

858
00:38:11,640 --> 00:38:13,757
Hell, I can hit 43 home runs right now.

859
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:15,320
Not off no major-league pitcher,
you couldn't.

860
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:16,959
We had better pitching
in the Negro leagues.

861
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,793
I hit seven home runs
off of Satchel Paige.

862
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:20,109
You can't get no better than that.

863
00:38:20,200 --> 00:38:21,873
Sandy Koufax,
he leading the league in strikeouts.

864
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:23,474
I ain't thinking about no Sandy Koufax.

865
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:25,313
You got Warren Spahn
and Lew Burdette. I bet you...

866
00:38:25,400 --> 00:38:26,629
I'm through with it now.

867
00:38:30,880 --> 00:38:33,270
Go and cut them boards.

868
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:38,677
Your mama told me you got
recruited by a college football team.

869
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:40,080
Is that right?

870
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:43,512
Yeah, Coach Zellman say the recruiter
gonna be coming by to talk to you.

871
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:45,637
Get you to sign the permission papers.

872
00:38:45,760 --> 00:38:47,319
I thought you was supposed to
be working down the A&P.

873
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:49,039
Ain't you supposed to be
working down there after school?

874
00:38:49,120 --> 00:38:50,873
Mr. Stawicki say
he gonna hold my job for me

875
00:38:50,960 --> 00:38:52,360
until after the football season.

876
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:55,030
He said starting next week,
I can work weekends.

877
00:38:55,120 --> 00:38:58,033
Boy, I thought we had an understanding
about this football stuff.

878
00:38:58,120 --> 00:38:59,839
You supposed to keep up with your chores,

879
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:01,718
hold your job down there at the A&P.

880
00:39:01,800 --> 00:39:03,996
You ain't been around here all day
on a Saturday,

881
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:05,355
ain't none of your chores done.

882
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:07,113
Now you come telling me
you done quit your job?

883
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:09,277
- I'm gonna be working weekends.
- You damn right you are!

884
00:39:09,360 --> 00:39:11,192
And ain't no need for nobody
to be coming around here,

885
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:12,430
talking to me about signing nothing.

886
00:39:12,520 --> 00:39:13,556
Pop, you can't do that.

887
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:14,915
He's coming all the way
from North Carolina.

888
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:16,872
I don't care where he coming from!

889
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:18,150
Look, boy,

890
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:20,680
the white man ain't gonna let you

891
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:22,558
get nowhere with no football no way.

892
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:25,156
Now you get your book-learning, so you can

893
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:28,193
work your way up at the A&P
and learn how to fix cars,

894
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:29,953
or build houses, get you a trade.

895
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:32,555
This way, you got something
can't nobody take away from you.

896
00:39:32,680 --> 00:39:35,070
You go in and learn how to
put your hands to good use

897
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:37,038
besides hauling other people's garbage.

898
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:38,190
I get good grades, Pop.

899
00:39:38,280 --> 00:39:39,634
That's why the recruiter
want to talk with you.

900
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:41,279
You got to keep up
your grades to get recruited.

901
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:43,192
This way, I'll be going to college,
I'll get a chance.

902
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:46,751
First, you get your butt down there
and get your job back.

903
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:48,274
Mr. Stawicki done already
hired somebody else

904
00:39:48,360 --> 00:39:49,794
'cause I told him I was playing football.

905
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:53,272
You a bigger fool than I thought.

906
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:55,352
You gonna let somebody take away your job,

907
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:56,760
so you can play some football.

908
00:39:57,320 --> 00:40:00,120
Where you gonna get your money to take
care of your girlfriend and whatnot?

909
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:01,554
What kind of foolishness is that

910
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:03,074
to let somebody take away your job?

911
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:04,389
I'm still gonna be working weekends.

912
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:06,551
No. You getting out of here
and finding you another job.

913
00:40:06,640 --> 00:40:07,915
Come on, Pop. I gotta practice.

914
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,753
I can't work after school
and play football, too.

915
00:40:09,840 --> 00:40:11,399
The team needs me,
that's what Coach Zellman say.

916
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:13,631
I don't care what nobody say.
I'm the boss. You understand?

917
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:16,952
I'm the boss around here.
I do the only saying what counts.

918
00:40:17,040 --> 00:40:19,430
- Come on...
- I asked you, "Do you understand?"

919
00:40:19,560 --> 00:40:22,439
- Yeah.
- What?

920
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:25,672
- Yes, sir.
- All right.

921
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:28,790
You get on down there to that A&P
and see if you can get your job back.

922
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:31,440
If you can't do both,
then you quit the football team.

923
00:40:31,520 --> 00:40:33,637
You got to take the crookeds
with the straights.

924
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:34,915
Yes, sir.

925
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:45,592
- Can I ask you a question?
- What the hell you got to ask me?

926
00:40:45,680 --> 00:40:48,479
Mr. Stawicki the one
you got the questions for.

927
00:40:48,560 --> 00:40:50,040
How come you ain't never liked me?

928
00:40:51,240 --> 00:40:55,473
Like you?
Who the hell said I got to like you?

929
00:40:56,960 --> 00:40:59,111
What law is there say I got to like you?

930
00:40:59,200 --> 00:41:02,319
You want to stand up in front of my face
and ask a damn fool-ass question like that.

931
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:03,675
Talk about liking somebody.

932
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:05,080
Come here, boy, when I talk to you.

933
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:11,719
Straighten up, God damn it!
I asked you a question.

934
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:14,959
- What law is there say I got to like you?
- None.

935
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:17,032
All right, then. Don't you eat every day?

936
00:41:18,400 --> 00:41:19,834
Answer me when I talk to you.

937
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:20,956
- Don't you eat every day?
- Yeah.

938
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:22,753
Nigger, as long as you in my house,

939
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:24,832
you put a "sir" on the end of it
when you talk to me.

940
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:26,314
- Yes, sir.
- You eat every day?

