00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:27,720
- Got a roof over your head?
- Yes, sir.

942
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:28,995
- Got clothes on your back?
- Yes, sir.

943
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:30,560
- Why you think that is?
- 'Cause of you.

944
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:35,240
Hell, I know it's 'cause of me.
But why do you think that is?

945
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:38,240
'Cause you like me?

946
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:40,352
"Like" you.

947
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:42,318
I go out of here every morning,

948
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:45,711
I bust my butt putting up
with them crackers every day

949
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:47,519
'cause I "like" you.

950
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:50,638
You about the biggest fool I ever saw.
It's my job.

951
00:41:50,720 --> 00:41:52,552
It's my responsibility.

952
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:55,439
A man is supposed to
take care of his family.

953
00:41:55,640 --> 00:41:58,519
You live in my house,
fill your belly with my food,

954
00:41:58,600 --> 00:42:02,196
put your behind on my bed
because you're my son.

955
00:42:02,280 --> 00:42:05,079
Not 'cause I like you.
'Cause it's my duty to take care of you.

956
00:42:05,160 --> 00:42:07,720
I owe a responsibility to you.

957
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:09,678
Now, let's get this straight
right here and now,

958
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:11,319
before it go along any further.

959
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:12,880
I ain't got to like you.

960
00:42:12,960 --> 00:42:16,078
Mr. Rand don't give me my money
come payday 'cause he like me.

961
00:42:16,160 --> 00:42:19,198
He give it to me 'cause he owe me.

962
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:21,319
Now I done give you everything
I got to give you.

963
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:23,710
I give you your life!

964
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:25,280
Me and your mama
worked that out between us,

965
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:28,478
and liking your black ass
wasn't part of the bargain.

966
00:42:28,680 --> 00:42:30,080
Now don't you go through life

967
00:42:30,160 --> 00:42:32,391
worrying about
whether somebody like you, or not.

968
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:35,552
You best be making sure
they're doing right by you.

969
00:42:35,640 --> 00:42:37,279
- You understand what I'm saying?
- Yes, sir.

970
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:40,797
Then get the hell out of my face
and get on down to that A&P!

971
00:43:04,160 --> 00:43:06,595
Why don't you go ahead
and let the boy play football, Troy?

972
00:43:06,680 --> 00:43:08,592
He just want to be like you
with the sports.

973
00:43:08,680 --> 00:43:10,751
I don't want him to be like me.

974
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:12,433
I want him to get as far away from my life

975
00:43:12,520 --> 00:43:13,590
as he possibly can get.

976
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:15,831
You the only decent thing
ever happened to me, Rose.

977
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:17,794
And I wish him that.

978
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:21,512
But I don't wish him
nothing else from my life.

979
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:26,434
I decided 17 years ago, that boy
wasn't gonna get involved in no sports.

980
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:28,159
Not after
what they did to me in the sports.

981
00:43:28,240 --> 00:43:30,471
Why don't you just admit
you were too old for the major leagues?

982
00:43:30,560 --> 00:43:32,153
For once, why don't you just admit that?

983
00:43:32,240 --> 00:43:33,913
Don't you come tellin' me I was too old.

984
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:37,232
I just wasn't the right color.
Hell, I'm 53 years old,

985
00:43:37,360 --> 00:43:40,432
I can do better than Selkirk's .269
right now.

986
00:43:40,520 --> 00:43:42,876
How were you gonna play ball
when you were over 40?

987
00:43:42,960 --> 00:43:44,633
Sometimes, I can't get
no sense out of you.

988
00:43:44,720 --> 00:43:45,790
I got good sense, woman.

989
00:43:45,880 --> 00:43:49,112
I got sense enough not to let that boy
get hurt playing no sports.

990
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:50,714
You mothering the boy too much.

991
00:43:50,840 --> 00:43:52,957
Worrying about whether people
"like" him or not.

992
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:56,317
Everything that boy do, he do for you.

993
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:58,960
He wants you to say, "Good job, son."
That's all.

994
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:02,518
I ain't got time for that, Rose.
He's alive, he's healthy.

995
00:44:02,600 --> 00:44:05,957
He's got to make his own way. I made mine.

996
00:44:06,080 --> 00:44:08,595
Ain't nobody gonna hold his hand
when he get out there in the world.

997
00:44:08,680 --> 00:44:11,036
Times have changed, Troy.

998
00:44:11,120 --> 00:44:13,191
People change.

999
00:44:13,280 --> 00:44:15,556
The world changing,
and you can't even see it.

1000
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:24,834
Woman, I do the best I can do.

1001
00:44:24,920 --> 00:44:26,240
I come in here every Friday,

1002
00:44:26,320 --> 00:44:29,154
I carry a sack of potatoes
and a bucket of lard.

1003
00:44:29,240 --> 00:44:32,836
You all line up at the door
with your hands out.

1004
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:36,516
I give you the lint from my pockets.
I give you my sweat and my blood.

1005
00:44:36,600 --> 00:44:39,195
I ain't got no tears. I done spent them.

1006
00:44:39,320 --> 00:44:41,915
We go upstairs in that room at night,
I fall down on you

1007
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:45,516
and try to blast a hole into forever.

1008
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:47,831
I get up Monday morning,
find my lunch on the table,

1009
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:49,320
go out and make my way.

1010
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:53,679
Find my strength
to get me through to next Friday.

1011
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:55,160
That's all I got, Rose.

1012
00:44:58,280 --> 00:45:01,079
That's all I got to give.

1013
00:45:05,280 --> 00:45:06,794
Can't give nothing else!

1014
00:45:33,720 --> 00:45:34,995
Mr. Maxson?

1015
00:45:37,920 --> 00:45:40,116
Commissioner will see you now.

1016
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:48,274
Rose!

1017
00:45:51,240 --> 00:45:52,833
Hey, Ro!

1018
00:45:52,920 --> 00:45:57,312
I wish I could've seen Mr. Rand's face
when he told you.

1019
00:45:57,440 --> 00:46:00,194
He couldn't get it out his mouth.
Liked to bit his tongue.

1020
00:46:00,280 --> 00:46:02,192
When they called me down there
to the Commissioner's office,

1021
00:46:02,320 --> 00:46:05,074
he thought they was gonna fire me,
like everybody else.

1022
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:06,799
I didn't think they was gonna fire you.

1023
00:46:06,880 --> 00:46:09,349
I thought they's gonna put you
on the warning paper.

1024
00:46:09,440 --> 00:46:12,751
Hey, Rose!
Yeah, Mr. Rand liked to bit his tongue.

1025
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:14,877
I see you run right down there to Taylors'

1026
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:16,275
and told that Alberta gal.

1027
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:19,432
Hey, Rose! I told everybody. Hey, Ro!

1028
00:46:19,520 --> 00:46:21,432
I went down there to cash my check.

1029
00:46:22,320 --> 00:46:23,356
Hey!

1030
00:46:23,440 --> 00:46:25,238
Hush all that hollering.
I know you out here.

1031
00:46:25,320 --> 00:46:27,118
What they say down
at the Commissioner's office?

1032
00:46:27,200 --> 00:46:28,998
You supposed to come
when I call you, woman.

1033
00:46:29,080 --> 00:46:30,230
Bono will tell you that.

1034
00:46:30,320 --> 00:46:31,834
Don't Lucille come when you call her?

1035
00:46:31,920 --> 00:46:33,036
Man, hush your mouth. I ain't no dog.

1036
00:46:33,120 --> 00:46:34,440
Talk about come when you call me.

1037
00:46:34,560 --> 00:46:36,074
You hear this, Bono?
I used to have me an old dog

1038
00:46:36,160 --> 00:46:37,230
get uppity like that.

1039
00:46:37,320 --> 00:46:39,880
You say, "Come here, Blue,"
he just lay there, look at you.

1040
00:46:39,960 --> 00:46:42,191
End up getting a stick chasin' him away,
trying to make him come.

1041
00:46:42,320 --> 00:46:43,800
I ain't studying you and your dog.

1042
00:46:43,880 --> 00:46:45,473
I remember you used to sing that old song.

1043
00:46:45,720 --> 00:46:47,871
<i>Hear it ring! Hear it ring!</i>

1044
00:46:48,080 --> 00:46:49,753
<i>Had an old dog, his name was Blue</i>

1045
00:46:49,840 --> 00:46:51,354
Nobody wants to hear that old song.

1046
00:46:52,320 --> 00:46:54,073
<i>You know Blue was mighty true</i>

1047
00:46:54,160 --> 00:46:56,231
Used to have Cory runnin' around here
singin' that song.

1048
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:57,993
Hell, I remember that song myself.

1049
00:46:58,080 --> 00:47:00,436
<i>You know Blue was a good old dog</i>

1050
00:47:00,640 --> 00:47:02,836
<i>Blue treed a possum in a hollow log</i>

1051
00:47:03,000 --> 00:47:05,515
That's my daddy's song.
My daddy made up that song.

1052
00:47:05,600 --> 00:47:08,160
I don't care who made it up.
Don't nobody want to hear you sing it.

1053
00:47:08,480 --> 00:47:09,834
<i>Come here, woman!</i>

1054
00:47:10,160 --> 00:47:13,631
You come in here carrying on,
I reckon they ain't fired you.

1055
00:47:13,720 --> 00:47:15,677
What they say down there
at the Commissioner's office?

1056
00:47:15,760 --> 00:47:18,798
Look here, Rose.
Mr. Rand called me in his office

1057
00:47:18,880 --> 00:47:21,395
after I got back from
talkin' to them people down there.

1058
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:23,790
He called me in his office and told me...

1059
00:47:25,520 --> 00:47:26,920
They was making me a driver!

1060
00:47:27,520 --> 00:47:30,433
- Troy, you kidding!
- No, I ain't. Ask Bono.

1061
00:47:30,520 --> 00:47:33,154
That's great, Troy. Now you don't
have to hassle them people no more.

1062
00:47:33,240 --> 00:47:36,358
Oh, hell.
I didn't think I was gonna see you today.

1063
00:47:36,440 --> 00:47:37,920
I thought you was in jail.

1064
00:47:38,040 --> 00:47:40,350
Got it all over the <i>Courier</i>
about them raiding Seefus' place

1065
00:47:40,440 --> 00:47:42,955
where you be hanging out
with all them thugs.

1066
00:47:43,040 --> 00:47:44,679
Hey, Pop,
that ain't got nothing to do with me.

1067
00:47:44,880 --> 00:47:46,075
I don't go down there gambling.

1068
00:47:46,160 --> 00:47:48,038
I just go down there
to sit in with the band.

1069
00:47:48,120 --> 00:47:50,191
I ain't got nothing to do
with the gambling part.

1070
00:47:50,280 --> 00:47:51,794
They got some good music down there.

1071
00:47:51,880 --> 00:47:53,633
They got some rogues is what they got.

1072
00:47:53,720 --> 00:47:55,712
How you been, Mr. Bono? Hi, Rose.

1073
00:47:55,800 --> 00:47:58,440
I see where you playing down
at the Crawford Grill tonight.

1074
00:47:58,560 --> 00:48:00,040
How come you ain't brought
Bonnie like I told you?

1075
00:48:00,120 --> 00:48:01,110
You shoulda brought Bonnie.

1076
00:48:01,200 --> 00:48:02,520
She ain't been by in a month of Sundays.

1077
00:48:02,600 --> 00:48:03,795
I was just in the neighborhood.

1078
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:05,280
- Thought I'd stop by.
- Here it comes.

1079
00:48:05,400 --> 00:48:07,596
Your daddy got a promotion on the rubbish.

1080
00:48:07,680 --> 00:48:09,990
He gonna be the first colored driver.

1081
00:48:10,080 --> 00:48:12,874
Ain't got to do nothin' but sit up there and
read the paper, like them white fellas.

1082
00:48:12,960 --> 00:48:15,680
Hey, Pop, if you knew
how to read, you'd be all right.

1083
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:18,275
Nah, nah. You mean
if the nigger knew how to drive,

1084
00:48:18,360 --> 00:48:19,476
he'd be all right.

1085
00:48:19,720 --> 00:48:23,113
Been fighting with them people about
driving and ain't even got a license.

1086
00:48:23,200 --> 00:48:24,919
Mr. Rand know
you ain't got no driver's license?

1087
00:48:25,000 --> 00:48:25,990
Driving ain't nothing.

1088
00:48:26,080 --> 00:48:27,833
All you do is point the truck
where you want it to go.

1089
00:48:27,920 --> 00:48:28,990
Driving ain't nothing.

1090
00:48:29,080 --> 00:48:30,594
Do they know
you ain't got no driver's license?

1091
00:48:30,720 --> 00:48:31,790
That's what I'm talkin' about.

1092
00:48:31,880 --> 00:48:33,234
I ain't asked if driving was easy.

1093
00:48:33,320 --> 00:48:35,676
I asked if Mr. Rand know
you ain't got no driver's license.

1094
00:48:35,760 --> 00:48:36,830
The man ain't got to know my business.

1095
00:48:36,920 --> 00:48:39,071
Time he find out, I have
two or three of them driver's license.

1096
00:48:39,160 --> 00:48:41,038
- Say, look here, Pop.
- I knew it was coming.

1097
00:48:41,120 --> 00:48:43,032
I knew what kinda "Look here, Pop"
that was.

1098
00:48:43,120 --> 00:48:44,440
Nigger finna ask me for some money.

1099
00:48:44,680 --> 00:48:46,399
It's Friday night, it's my payday.

1100
00:48:46,480 --> 00:48:49,996
All them rogues down on the avenue,
the ones that ain't in jail,

1101
00:48:50,080 --> 00:48:52,800
and Lyons is hopping in his shoes
to get down there with them.

1102
00:48:52,880 --> 00:48:53,916
Now, see, Pop,

1103
00:48:54,000 --> 00:48:56,515
if you gave somebody else
a chance to talk sometime,

1104
00:48:56,600 --> 00:49:00,196
you'd see I was fixing to pay you back
your $10 like I told you.

1105
00:49:00,280 --> 00:49:03,432
Here. I told you I'd pay you
when Bonnie got paid.

1106
00:49:03,520 --> 00:49:05,716
No, you keep that $10. Put it in the bank.

1107
00:49:05,800 --> 00:49:07,393
Next time you feel like
you wanna come by here

1108
00:49:07,480 --> 00:49:09,119
and ask me for somethin',
you go down there and get that.

1109
00:49:09,440 --> 00:49:10,669
Here you go your $10, Pop.

1110
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:12,553
I told you,
I don't want you to give me nothing.

1111
00:49:12,640 --> 00:49:13,869
I just wanted to borrow $10.

1112
00:49:13,960 --> 00:49:16,520
No, you keep that for the next time
you want to ask me.

1113
00:49:16,800 --> 00:49:18,120
Come on, Pop, here go your $10.

1114
00:49:18,200 --> 00:49:21,272
Troy, why don't you let the boy
pay you back?

1115
00:49:24,120 --> 00:49:26,680
Here you go, Rose. If you don't take it,

1116
00:49:26,760 --> 00:49:28,717
I'm gonna hear about it
for the next six months.

1117
00:49:28,800 --> 00:49:30,439
You can hand yours over, too, Troy.

1118
00:49:30,520 --> 00:49:32,034
You see this, Bono?
You see how they do me?

1119
00:49:32,120 --> 00:49:33,873
Yeah, Lucille do me the same way.

1120
00:49:34,000 --> 00:49:37,311
<i>Better get ready for the Judgment</i>

1121
00:49:38,800 --> 00:49:40,359
<i>Better get ready</i>

1122
00:49:43,160 --> 00:49:45,152
Hey. Hey, there's Troy's boy!

1123
00:49:45,240 --> 00:49:46,560
How you doing, Uncle Gabe?

1124
00:49:46,640 --> 00:49:48,120
Lyons!

1125
00:49:50,080 --> 00:49:52,436
The King of the Jungle!

1126
00:49:52,840 --> 00:49:55,719
Rose. Hey, Rose, I got a flower for you.

1127
00:49:55,800 --> 00:49:58,235
I picked it myself.
That's the same rose like you is.

1128
00:49:58,320 --> 00:49:59,993
That's right nice of you, Gabe.

1129
00:50:00,080 --> 00:50:01,594
What you been doing, Uncle Gabe?

1130
00:50:01,680 --> 00:50:05,151
I been chasing hellhounds
and waiting for the time

1131
00:50:05,240 --> 00:50:07,072
to tell Saint Peter to open the Gates.

1132
00:50:07,160 --> 00:50:08,833
You been chasing hellhounds, huh?

1133
00:50:08,920 --> 00:50:10,639
Well, you doing
the right thing, Uncle Gabe.

1134
00:50:10,720 --> 00:50:13,713
- Somebody's got to chase 'em.
- Yeah, I know it.

1135
00:50:13,800 --> 00:50:16,679
The devil's strong.
The devil ain't no pushover.

1136
00:50:16,760 --> 00:50:19,195
Hellhounds snipping at everybody's heels.

1137
00:50:19,280 --> 00:50:21,875
But I got my trumpet waiting
on the Judgment time.

1138
00:50:21,960 --> 00:50:23,679
Waiting on the Battle of Armageddon, huh?

1139
00:50:23,760 --> 00:50:25,831
Ain't gonna be too much of a battle

1140
00:50:25,960 --> 00:50:29,397
when God get to waving
that Judgment sword.

1141
00:50:29,480 --> 00:50:31,551
But the people's
gonna have a hell of a time

1142
00:50:31,640 --> 00:50:34,200
trying to get into Heaven
if them Gates ain't open.

1143
00:50:34,280 --> 00:50:35,794
You hear this, Pop?

1144
00:50:36,360 --> 00:50:38,556
- Uncle Gabe, you all right.
- Lyons.

1145
00:50:41,680 --> 00:50:44,115
- The King of the Jungle!
- You stayin' for supper, Gabe?

1146
00:50:44,200 --> 00:50:45,270
You want me to fix you a plate?

1147
00:50:45,360 --> 00:50:48,273
I'll just take a sandwich, Rose.
I don't want no plate.

1148
00:50:48,360 --> 00:50:50,477
I want to eat with my hands.
I'll take a sandwich.

1149
00:50:50,560 --> 00:50:52,950
What about you, Lyons? You stayin'?
Got some short ribs cooking.

1150
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:56,511
Nah. I won't eat nothing
till after we finish playing.

1151
00:50:57,160 --> 00:50:59,152
You ought to come down,
listen to me play, Pop.

1152
00:50:59,240 --> 00:51:01,516
I don't like all that Chinese music,
all that noise.

1153
00:51:01,600 --> 00:51:05,071
Go in there and wash up, Gabe.
I'll fix you a sandwich.

1154
00:51:05,160 --> 00:51:07,800
Troy mad at me.

1155
00:51:07,880 --> 00:51:09,234
What you mad at Uncle Gabe for?

1156
00:51:09,320 --> 00:51:12,154
He think Troy mad at him 'cause
he moved over there to Miss Pearl's.

1157
00:51:12,240 --> 00:51:14,311
I ain't mad at the man.
He can live where he want to live at.

1158
00:51:14,400 --> 00:51:16,551
Well, what he move over there for?
Miss Pearl don't like nobody.

1159
00:51:16,640 --> 00:51:18,393
She don't mind him none.
She treat him real nice.

1160
00:51:18,480 --> 00:51:19,960
She just don't allow all that singing.

1161
00:51:20,040 --> 00:51:22,600
She don't mind that rent he be paying.
That's what she don't mind.

1162
00:51:22,680 --> 00:51:24,194
Troy, I ain't goin' through that
with you no more.

1163
00:51:24,280 --> 00:51:26,078
He moved over there
'cause he wanted his own place.

1164
00:51:26,160 --> 00:51:27,230
He can come and go as he please.

1165
00:51:27,320 --> 00:51:29,437
He can come and go as he please here.
I wasn't stoppin' him.

1166
00:51:29,520 --> 00:51:30,749
I wasn't putting no rules on the man.

1167
00:51:30,840 --> 00:51:32,593
That ain't the same thing,
and you know it.

1168
00:51:32,680 --> 00:51:33,909
Now that's the last
I wanna hear about that.

1169
00:51:34,000 --> 00:51:36,151
I don't wanna hear nothin' else
about Gabe and Miss Pearl.

1170
00:51:36,280 --> 00:51:38,920
- And next week...
- I'm ready for my sandwich, Rose.

1171
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:41,151
And next week, when
that recruiter come from that school,

1172
00:51:41,240 --> 00:51:43,914
I want you to sign that paper
and go on and let Cory play football.

1173
00:51:44,000 --> 00:51:45,719
That'll be the last
I have to hear about that.

1174
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:52,392
Cory got recruited?
What school he goin' to?

1175
00:51:52,520 --> 00:51:54,113
I ain't thinking about Cory nothing.

1176
00:51:54,200 --> 00:51:57,920
Boy walking around here smelling his piss,
thinking he gonna do what he want to do,

1177
00:51:58,000 --> 00:52:00,276
irregardless of what I say.

1178
00:52:00,360 --> 00:52:02,636
Look here, Bono,
I left the Commissioner's office

1179
00:52:02,720 --> 00:52:04,120
and went down to the A&P.

1180
00:52:04,200 --> 00:52:06,396
That boy ain't workin' down there,
he lied to me.

1181
00:52:06,480 --> 00:52:09,837
Tellin' me he got his job back,
tellin' me he workin' weekend,

1182
00:52:09,920 --> 00:52:11,479
tellin' me he workin' after school.

1183
00:52:11,560 --> 00:52:13,791
Mr. Stawicki says
he ain't working down there at all.

1184
00:52:13,880 --> 00:52:15,075
Cory just growing up.

1185
00:52:15,160 --> 00:52:17,197
He just bustin' at the seams,
tryin' to fill out your shoes.

1186
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:18,470
I don't care what he doing.

1187
00:52:18,560 --> 00:52:20,631
When he get to the place
where he want to disobey me,

1188
00:52:20,720 --> 00:52:23,872
then it's time for him to move on.
Bono will tell you that.

1189
00:52:23,960 --> 00:52:27,636
I bet he ain't never disobeyed his daddy
without paying the consequences.

1190
00:52:27,720 --> 00:52:29,996
I ain't never had the chance.

1191
00:52:30,080 --> 00:52:33,676
My daddy came on through,
but I ain't never knew him to see him.

1192
00:52:33,760 --> 00:52:36,355
Or what he had on his mind,
or where he went.

1193
00:52:36,440 --> 00:52:40,116
Just moving on through.
Searching out the New Land.

1194
00:52:41,000 --> 00:52:43,310
That's what the old folks used to call it.

1195
00:52:43,400 --> 00:52:46,837
See a fella moving around
from place to place, woman to woman,

1196
00:52:46,920 --> 00:52:49,310
they call it "Searching out the New Land."

1197
00:52:49,400 --> 00:52:51,039
I can't say if he ever found it.

1198
00:52:51,800 --> 00:52:54,269
I come along, didn't want no kids.

1199
00:52:54,760 --> 00:52:56,752
I didn't know if I was gonna
be in one place long enough

1200
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:58,832
to fix on 'em right as their daddy.

1201
00:52:58,920 --> 00:53:01,037
I figured I was going searching, too.

1202
00:53:01,120 --> 00:53:03,351
As it turn out,
I been hooked up with Lucille

1203
00:53:03,440 --> 00:53:05,830
for near about as long as
your daddy been with Rose.

1204
00:53:05,920 --> 00:53:08,071
Going on 16 years.

1205
00:53:08,160 --> 00:53:10,038
Sometimes, I wish
I'd never known my daddy.

1206
00:53:10,120 --> 00:53:13,875
He ain't cared nothing about no kids.
A kid to him wasn't nothing.

1207
00:53:14,280 --> 00:53:17,432
All he wanted you to do
was learn how to walk,

1208
00:53:17,520 --> 00:53:19,193
so he could start you to working.

1209
00:53:19,280 --> 00:53:23,035
Come to eating, he ate first.
Anything left over, that's what you got.

1210
00:53:23,120 --> 00:53:26,192
Man would sit down, eat two chickens,
and give you the wing.

1211
00:53:26,280 --> 00:53:29,557
You ought to stop that, Pop.
Everybody feed their kids.

1212
00:53:29,640 --> 00:53:32,758
No matter how hard times is,
everybody care about their kids.

1213
00:53:32,840 --> 00:53:34,035
Make sure they have something to eat.

1214
00:53:34,120 --> 00:53:35,873
Only thing my daddy cared about

1215
00:53:35,960 --> 00:53:37,713
was getting them bales
of cotton in to Mr. Lubin.

1216
00:53:37,800 --> 00:53:39,837
That's the only thing
that mattered to him.

1217
00:53:39,920 --> 00:53:42,071
Sometimes, I used to wonder
why he was still living,

1218
00:53:42,160 --> 00:53:44,720
why the devil hadn't come and got him.

1219
00:53:44,960 --> 00:53:46,872
"Get them bales of cotton
in to Mr. Lubin."

1220
00:53:46,960 --> 00:53:48,314
Find out he owe him money.

1221
00:53:48,400 --> 00:53:50,596
He should have just went on and left
when he saw he couldn't get nowhere.

1222
00:53:50,680 --> 00:53:51,716
That's what I would've done.

1223
00:53:51,800 --> 00:53:54,713
How he gonna leave with 11 kids?
And where he gonna go?

1224
00:53:54,800 --> 00:53:57,998
He ain't knew nothing but how to farm.
No, he was trapped.

1225
00:53:58,400 --> 00:54:01,552
I think he knew it, too.
But I'll say this for him...

1226
00:54:01,640 --> 00:54:03,393
He felt a responsibility toward us.

1227
00:54:03,480 --> 00:54:05,472
May not have treated us
like I felt he should have,

1228
00:54:05,560 --> 00:54:09,474
but without that responsibility,
he could have run off and left us,

1229
00:54:09,600 --> 00:54:10,920
made his own way.

1230
00:54:11,000 --> 00:54:12,400
A lot of them did.

1231
00:54:12,480 --> 00:54:14,073
Back in those days,
what you talkin' about?

1232
00:54:14,160 --> 00:54:15,799
They walk out their front door

1233
00:54:15,880 --> 00:54:19,078
and take off down one road or another
and just keep on walkin'.

1234
00:54:19,160 --> 00:54:21,072
There you go.
That's what I'm talkin' about.

1235
00:54:21,160 --> 00:54:24,517
Just keep on walking
till they come to something else.

1236
00:54:24,600 --> 00:54:27,911
Ain't you never heard of nobody
having the walking blues?

1237
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:30,469
Now, that's what you call it
when you just take off like that.

1238
00:54:31,120 --> 00:54:34,431
My daddy ain't had no walking blues.
What you talking about?

1239
00:54:34,520 --> 00:54:36,000
He stayed right there with his family,

1240
00:54:36,840 --> 00:54:40,754
but he was just as evil as he could be!

1241
00:54:40,880 --> 00:54:44,510
My mama couldn't stand him.
Couldn't stand that evilness.

1242
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:47,593
She run off when I was about eight.

1243
00:54:47,720 --> 00:54:50,838
She sneaked off one night,
told me she was coming back for me.

1244
00:54:50,920 --> 00:54:52,639
I ain't never seen her no more.

1245
00:54:52,720 --> 00:54:56,839
All his women run off and left him.
He wasn't good for nobody.

1246
00:54:57,360 --> 00:54:59,033
My turn come to head out.

1247
00:54:59,120 --> 00:55:00,474
I was 14,

1248
00:55:00,560 --> 00:55:03,439
got to sniffing around
Joe Canewell's daughter.

1249
00:55:04,800 --> 00:55:07,110
We had this old mule called "Greyboy".

1250
00:55:07,240 --> 00:55:09,357
My daddy sent me out to do some plowing.

1251
00:55:09,440 --> 00:55:13,116
I got to fooling around
with Joe Canewell's daughter.

1252
00:55:13,200 --> 00:55:16,398
Found us a nice spot,
got real cozy with each other.

1253
00:55:16,480 --> 00:55:19,678
She was about 13,
so we done figured we grown anyway.

1254
00:55:19,760 --> 00:55:22,150
So, we were down there by
the creek, enjoying ourselves,

1255
00:55:22,240 --> 00:55:23,640
ain't thinking about nothing.

1256
00:55:23,720 --> 00:55:26,030
Didn't know Greyboy had gotten loose,

1257
00:55:26,120 --> 00:55:29,557
wandered back to the house,
and my daddy was lookin' for me.

1258
00:55:29,840 --> 00:55:33,311
So, we down there enjoying ourselves
when he come up on us.

1259
00:55:33,400 --> 00:55:35,471
Surprised us.

1260
00:55:35,600 --> 00:55:38,115
Had them leather straps off that mule,

1261
00:55:38,200 --> 00:55:41,238
commenced to whupping me
like there was no tomorrow.

1262
00:55:41,320 --> 00:55:43,915
I jump up. I'm mad, embarrassed.

1263
00:55:44,600 --> 00:55:46,717
I was scared of my daddy.

1264
00:55:46,920 --> 00:55:48,912
Now, when he commenced to whipping on me,

1265
00:55:49,000 --> 00:55:50,719
quite naturally,
I run to get out of the way.

1266
00:55:50,800 --> 00:55:53,474
Now, I think he's mad
'cause I ain't done my work.

1267
00:55:53,560 --> 00:55:58,191
But I see where he's chasing me off,
so he can have the gal for himself.

1268
00:55:59,600 --> 00:56:01,717
When I see what the matter of it was,

1269
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:06,879
I lost all fear of my daddy,
and right there, I became a man.

1270
00:56:06,960 --> 00:56:09,350
Fourteen years of age.

1271
00:56:09,440 --> 00:56:12,353
Now, it's my turn to run him off.

1272
00:56:12,440 --> 00:56:14,238
I picked up them same reins he used on me.

1273
00:56:14,320 --> 00:56:17,916
I picked up them reins,
I commenced to whupping on him.

1274
00:56:18,960 --> 00:56:21,270
Gal jump up, she run off.

1275
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:24,429
When he turned to face me,

1276
00:56:24,520 --> 00:56:26,398
I knew why the devil
never come and get him

1277
00:56:26,480 --> 00:56:28,631
'cause he was the devil himself.

1278
00:56:29,960 --> 00:56:32,520
I don't know what happened.

1279
00:56:32,600 --> 00:56:35,798
I woke up, laying there by the creek,

1280
00:56:35,880 --> 00:56:39,556
and Blue, this old dog we had,
he was licking my face.

1281
00:56:39,640 --> 00:56:42,678
Both my eyes were swoll shut.

1282
00:56:42,760 --> 00:56:44,592
I thought I was blind,
I couldn't see nothing.

1283
00:56:44,680 --> 00:56:48,390
I just laid there and cried.

1284
00:56:53,960 --> 00:56:56,873
And I didn't know what I was gonna do.

1285
00:56:56,960 --> 00:57:01,398
But I knew the time had come
for me to leave my daddy's house.

1286
00:57:02,680 --> 00:57:04,990
Suddenly, the world got big, and...

1287
00:57:08,080 --> 00:57:11,994
It was a long time before I could
cut it down to where I could handle it.

1288
00:57:13,680 --> 00:57:16,514
Part of that cutting down
was where I got to the place

1289
00:57:16,600 --> 00:57:18,592
where I could feel him
kicking in my blood,

1290
00:57:18,680 --> 00:57:20,273
and I knew the only thing
that separated us

1291
00:57:20,360 --> 00:57:22,477
was a matter of a few years.

1292
00:57:25,520 --> 00:57:26,874
What you got there, Uncle Gabe?

1293
00:57:27,880 --> 00:57:29,314
I got me a ham sandwich.

1294
00:57:29,400 --> 00:57:31,551
Rose gave me a ham sandwich.

1295
00:57:34,040 --> 00:57:36,191
I lost touch with everybody
except Gabriel.

1296
00:57:41,200 --> 00:57:42,190
But...

1297
00:57:45,880 --> 00:57:47,712
I hope he's dead.

1298
00:57:51,960 --> 00:57:54,634
I hope he found some peace.

1299
00:57:54,720 --> 00:57:56,757
That's a heavy story, Pop.

1300
00:57:58,160 --> 00:58:01,949
I didn't know you left home
when you was 14.

1301
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:04,117
Fourteen's kinda young to be on your own.

1302
00:58:04,200 --> 00:58:06,078
I don't know what I would've done.

1303
00:58:06,840 --> 00:58:09,639
Well, I got up from that creek,
walked on down to Mobile.

1304
00:58:09,720 --> 00:58:13,396
I was through with farming.
I figured I'd do better in the cities.

1305
00:58:13,480 --> 00:58:15,312
So, I walked the 200 miles to Mobile.

1306
00:58:15,400 --> 00:58:18,996
Wait a minute,
you ain't walked no 200 miles, Pop.

1307
00:58:19,080 --> 00:58:23,154
Ain't nobody gonna walk no 200 miles.
You talking about some walking there!

1308
00:58:23,240 --> 00:58:25,994
That's the only way you got anywhere
back in them days.

1309
00:58:26,080 --> 00:58:28,914
Shit! Damn if I wouldn't have
hitched a ride with somebody.

1310
00:58:29,000 --> 00:58:30,673
Who you gonna hitch it with?

1311
00:58:30,760 --> 00:58:32,558
There ain't no cars
and things like they got now.

1312
00:58:32,640 --> 00:58:34,279
We talking about 1918.

1313
00:58:34,360 --> 00:58:35,919
What you all out here gettin' into?

1314
00:58:36,000 --> 00:58:38,196
I'm telling Lyons how good he got it.

1315
00:58:38,280 --> 00:58:39,555
He don't know nothing
about this I'm talking.

1316
00:58:39,640 --> 00:58:42,394
Lyons, that was Bonnie on the phone.
She says you supposed to pick her up.

1317
00:58:42,480 --> 00:58:44,233
Yeah, okay, Rose.

1318
00:58:44,320 --> 00:58:47,040
I walked on down to Mobile,

1319
00:58:47,120 --> 00:58:50,397
hitched up with some fellows
that was coming up this way.

1320
00:58:50,480 --> 00:58:52,119
Got up here and found out,

1321
00:58:52,200 --> 00:58:53,714
not only could you not get a job,

1322
00:58:53,840 --> 00:58:55,354
you couldn't find no place to live.

1323
00:58:55,440 --> 00:58:58,080
I thought I was in freedom.

1324
00:58:58,360 --> 00:59:00,750
Colored folks living down there
on the riverbanks

1325
00:59:00,840 --> 00:59:03,071
in whatever kind of shelter
they could find for themselves.

1326
00:59:03,160 --> 00:59:05,629
Right down there
under the Brady Street Bridge.

1327
00:59:06,040 --> 00:59:09,351
Living down there in shacks
made out of sticks and tar paper.

1328
00:59:10,400 --> 00:59:12,119
Messed around down there.

1329
00:59:12,200 --> 00:59:14,715
Went from bad to worse. Started stealing.

1330
00:59:14,800 --> 00:59:17,395
First, it was food.
Then I figure I steal me some money,

1331
00:59:17,480 --> 00:59:19,949
I can buy me some food,
buy me some shoes, too.

1332
00:59:20,280 --> 00:59:22,033
One thing led to another. Met your mama.

1333
00:59:22,480 --> 00:59:24,790
I was young, anxious to be a man.

1334
00:59:25,360 --> 00:59:27,716
I met your mama and had you.
Why'd I do that for?

1335
00:59:27,800 --> 00:59:30,235
Now, I got to worry about
feeding you and her.

1336
00:59:30,320 --> 00:59:31,800
Got to steal three times as much.

1337
00:59:32,640 --> 00:59:36,031
I went out one day
looking for somebody to rob.

1338
00:59:36,160 --> 00:59:37,435
That's what I was, I was a robber.

1339
00:59:38,160 --> 00:59:39,753
I'mma tell you the truth.

1340
00:59:39,840 --> 00:59:41,752
I'm ashamed of it today,
but it's the truth.

1341
00:59:42,800 --> 00:59:44,678
I went to rob this fella,
I pull out my knife.

1342
00:59:44,760 --> 00:59:46,911
He pulled out a gun, shot me in the chest.

1343
00:59:47,000 --> 00:59:50,232
It felt like somebody had taken
a hot branding iron and laid it on me.

1344
00:59:50,320 --> 00:59:53,358
Now, when he shot me,
I jumped at him with my knife,

1345
00:59:55,240 --> 00:59:57,072
and they say I killed him.

1346
00:59:57,160 --> 00:59:59,231
Locked me up, put me in
the penitentiary for 15 years.

1347
00:59:59,320 --> 01:00:00,674
That's where I met Bono.

1348
01:00:01,240 --> 01:00:03,516
Where I learned how to play baseball.

1349
01:00:03,600 --> 01:00:05,114
Got out that place,
and your mama had taken you,

1350
01:00:05,200 --> 01:00:07,192
went on to make a life without me.

1351
01:00:07,280 --> 01:00:09,351
Fifteen years was a long time
for her to wait.

1352
01:00:09,440 --> 01:00:11,318
But that 15 years
cured me of that robbing stuff.

1353
01:00:11,400 --> 01:00:12,754
Rose'll tell you.

1354
01:00:12,840 --> 01:00:15,116
I first met her, she ask me if I had

1355
01:00:15,200 --> 01:00:17,351
gotten all that foolishness
out of my system.

1356
01:00:17,440 --> 01:00:19,272
I said, "Baby, it's you and baseball,

1357
01:00:19,360 --> 01:00:21,079
"all what count to me." You hear me, Bono?

1358
01:00:21,160 --> 01:00:23,800
And I meant it, too.
She said, "Which one come first?"

1359
01:00:23,880 --> 01:00:26,952
I said, "Well, ain't no doubt it's baseball.

1360
01:00:27,040 --> 01:00:28,997
"But you stick and get old with me,

1361
01:00:29,080 --> 01:00:30,639
"and we'll both outlive this baseball."

1362
01:00:30,720 --> 01:00:32,837
Am I right, Rose?

1363
01:00:34,040 --> 01:00:35,110
And it's true.

1364
01:00:35,200 --> 01:00:36,953
Man, hush your mouth.
You ain't say no such thing.

1365
01:00:37,040 --> 01:00:39,635
Talkin' about, "Baby, you know
you'll always be number one with me."

1366
01:00:39,720 --> 01:00:42,315
That's what you was talking.

1367
01:00:42,400 --> 01:00:44,869
- That's why I love this woman.
- Rose will keep you straight.

1368
01:00:44,960 --> 01:00:47,077
You get off the track,
she'll straighten you up.

1369
01:00:47,160 --> 01:00:48,514
Lyons, you better get on up
and get Bonnie.

1370
01:00:48,600 --> 01:00:50,080
She waiting on you.

1371
01:00:50,160 --> 01:00:51,435
- Hey, Pop.
- Yeah?

1372
01:00:51,520 --> 01:00:53,557
You ought to come down to the Grill,
hear me play.

1373
01:00:54,200 --> 01:00:55,919
Man, I ain't goin' down there.

1374
01:00:56,000 --> 01:00:57,434
I'm too old to be hanging out
in them clubs.

1375
01:00:57,520 --> 01:01:00,797
You got to be good to
play down at the Grill.

1376
01:01:00,880 --> 01:01:02,360
Come on, Pop.

1377
01:01:02,440 --> 01:01:06,229
- I got to get up in the morning.
- Well, you ain't gotta stay long.

1378
01:01:07,240 --> 01:01:10,916
No, I'm gonna eat my supper and go to bed.

1379
01:01:12,000 --> 01:01:14,834
Well, I got to go. I'll see you later.

1380
01:01:18,440 --> 01:01:20,636
Don't you come by my house on my payday!

1381
01:01:21,040 --> 01:01:23,111
And pick up the phone,
let somebody know you coming,

1382
01:01:23,240 --> 01:01:25,197
and bring Bonnie,
you know I'm always glad to see her.

1383
01:01:25,280 --> 01:01:28,751
I'll do that, Rose. You take care now.

1384
01:01:28,840 --> 01:01:30,354
- See you, Pop.
- All right.

1385
01:01:30,440 --> 01:01:32,511
See you, Mr. Bono.

1386
01:01:32,600 --> 01:01:35,638
- See you, Uncle Gabe!
- Lyons! King of the Jungle!

1387
01:01:36,880 --> 01:01:38,075
Supper ready, woman?

1388
01:01:38,160 --> 01:01:39,674
Me and you got some business
to take care of.

1389
01:01:39,800 --> 01:01:42,076
- I'mma tear it up, too.
- Troy, I done told you now!

1390
01:01:42,160 --> 01:01:46,313
Hell, woman, it's Bono. Bono like family.
I done know this nigger since...

1391
01:01:46,400 --> 01:01:48,869
- How long have I known you?
- It's been a long time.

1392
01:01:48,960 --> 01:01:51,350
I done known this nigger
since Skippy was a pup!

1393
01:01:51,440 --> 01:01:53,272
Me and him done been through some times!

1394
01:01:53,360 --> 01:01:55,033
You sure are right about that.

1395
01:01:55,120 --> 01:01:57,112
Hell, I known him
longer than I known you, Rose,

1396
01:01:57,200 --> 01:01:59,032
and we still standin'
shoulder to shoulder.

1397
01:01:59,120 --> 01:02:02,511
Look here, Bono,
a man can't ask for no more than that.

1398
