to hear something like this?

1632
01:15:06,080 --> 01:15:07,309
Hey, Rose.

1633
01:15:09,240 --> 01:15:11,596
I got a flower for you.

1634
01:15:14,280 --> 01:15:17,830
That's a rose. The same rose like you is.

1635
01:15:22,840 --> 01:15:24,274
Thanks, Gabe.

1636
01:15:24,360 --> 01:15:25,760
Troy, you ain't mad at me?

1637
01:15:25,840 --> 01:15:27,274
Them bad mens come and put me away.

1638
01:15:27,360 --> 01:15:29,750
- You ain't mad at me?
- No. No, I ain't mad at you.

1639
01:15:29,840 --> 01:15:31,752
Eighteen years,
and you want to come with this?

1640
01:15:31,880 --> 01:15:34,520
See what I got? Got a brand-new quarter.

1641
01:15:37,440 --> 01:15:38,510
Rose, it's just that...

1642
01:15:38,600 --> 01:15:40,796
Ain't nothing you can say, Troy.
Ain't no explaining it.

1643
01:15:40,880 --> 01:15:43,520
The fella that give me this quarter
had a whole mess of 'em!

1644
01:15:43,640 --> 01:15:46,109
I'm gonna keep this quarter
till it stops shining.

1645
01:15:46,200 --> 01:15:48,760
Gabe, go on up front now.
I got some watermelon in the Frigidaire.

1646
01:15:48,840 --> 01:15:49,990
Go on. I'll get you a piece.

1647
01:15:50,080 --> 01:15:52,800
Say, Rose, you know,
I was chasing hellhounds,

1648
01:15:52,880 --> 01:15:55,793
and them bad mens come
and get me and take me away.

1649
01:15:55,880 --> 01:15:57,872
Troy helped me.
He come down there and told them

1650
01:15:57,960 --> 01:16:00,873
they better let me go
before he beat them up!

1651
01:16:00,960 --> 01:16:02,235
Yeah, he did!

1652
01:16:02,320 --> 01:16:04,596
Go up front now, Gabe.
I'll get you some watermelon.

1653
01:16:04,680 --> 01:16:06,160
Them bad men is gone now.

1654
01:16:06,240 --> 01:16:08,596
Okay. Rose gonna give me some watermelon,

1655
01:16:08,680 --> 01:16:11,149
the kind with the stripes on it.

1656
01:16:16,640 --> 01:16:18,074
Why, Troy?

1657
01:16:19,840 --> 01:16:21,069
Why?

1658
01:16:21,160 --> 01:16:26,599
After all these years,
you come dragging this in to me now?

1659
01:16:26,680 --> 01:16:28,831
It don't make no sense at your age.

1660
01:16:29,520 --> 01:16:33,309
I could've expected this 10,
or 15 years ago, but not now.

1661
01:16:33,600 --> 01:16:35,831
Age ain't got nothing to do with it, Rose.

1662
01:16:39,920 --> 01:16:43,197
I done tried to be everything
a wife should be.

1663
01:16:45,200 --> 01:16:46,475
Everything a wife could be.

1664
01:16:46,560 --> 01:16:47,835
I've been married 18 years,

1665
01:16:47,920 --> 01:16:50,435
and now,
I got to live to see the day you tell me

1666
01:16:50,520 --> 01:16:54,036
you been seeing another woman
and done fathered a child by her.

1667
01:17:07,200 --> 01:17:11,194
And you know I never wanted
no half-nothing in my family!

1668
01:17:14,200 --> 01:17:15,475
My whole family is half.

1669
01:17:15,560 --> 01:17:17,392
Everybody got different
fathers and mothers

1670
01:17:17,480 --> 01:17:18,960
and my two sisters and my brothers.

1671
01:17:19,040 --> 01:17:20,633
You could hardly tell who's who.

1672
01:17:20,720 --> 01:17:22,473
Could never sit down
and talk about Papa and Mama.

1673
01:17:22,560 --> 01:17:25,200
It was always your papa,
your mama, my papa, my mama.

1674
01:17:25,280 --> 01:17:27,795
And I ain't never wanted that
for none of my children!

1675
01:17:27,880 --> 01:17:30,396
And now, you want to drag your behind
in here and tell me something like this!

1676
01:17:30,480 --> 01:17:32,437
Stop it now. You ought to know.
It's time for you to know.

1677
01:17:32,520 --> 01:17:34,239
Well, I don't want to know, God damn it!

1678
01:17:54,240 --> 01:17:55,310
Rose?

1679
01:17:58,440 --> 01:18:01,831
I just can't make it go away.
It's done now.

1680
01:18:01,920 --> 01:18:05,834
I can't wish the circumstances
of the thing away.

1681
01:18:06,000 --> 01:18:08,595
And you don't want to, either.

1682
01:18:08,680 --> 01:18:10,478
Maybe you want to wish me and my boy away.

1683
01:18:10,560 --> 01:18:11,914
Maybe that's what you want.

1684
01:18:12,040 --> 01:18:14,509
Well, you can't wish us away.

1685
01:18:14,600 --> 01:18:16,557
I got 18 years of my life invested in you.

1686
01:18:16,640 --> 01:18:18,677
You ought to have stayed upstairs
in my bed where you belong.

1687
01:18:18,760 --> 01:18:21,355
Now, listen to me.
We can get a handle on this thing.

1688
01:18:21,440 --> 01:18:23,272
We can talk this out,
come to an understanding.

1689
01:18:23,360 --> 01:18:24,589
All of a sudden it's "we."

1690
01:18:24,720 --> 01:18:25,949
Where was "we" at
when you were down there,

1691
01:18:26,040 --> 01:18:27,360
rolling around
with some godforsaken woman?

1692
01:18:27,440 --> 01:18:30,274
"We" should've come to an understanding before
you started making a damn fool of yourself!

1693
01:18:30,360 --> 01:18:33,234
You're a day late and a dollar short when
it comes to an understanding with me.

1694
01:18:33,320 --> 01:18:39,078
Rose, it's just that
she gives me a different idea.

1695
01:18:39,600 --> 01:18:42,752
A different understanding about myself.

1696
01:18:42,840 --> 01:18:46,311
I can step out of this house
and get away from the pressures

1697
01:18:46,400 --> 01:18:47,754
and the problems, be a different man.

1698
01:18:47,840 --> 01:18:49,638
I ain't got to worry about
how I'll get the roof fixed,

1699
01:18:49,720 --> 01:18:51,359
or pay the bills, or...

1700
01:18:51,440 --> 01:18:52,760
I can just

1701
01:18:54,720 --> 01:18:57,315
be a part of myself
I ain't never been before.

1702
01:18:58,520 --> 01:19:00,671
What I want to know is...

1703
01:19:03,200 --> 01:19:05,669
What I want to know

1704
01:19:05,800 --> 01:19:08,440
is do you plan to continue seeing her?

1705
01:19:08,520 --> 01:19:10,830
That's all you can say to me.

1706
01:19:12,120 --> 01:19:16,194
I could sit up in her house and laugh.
You understand what I'm saying?

1707
01:19:16,280 --> 01:19:18,875
I could laugh out loud, and it feels good.

1708
01:19:18,960 --> 01:19:21,191
It reaches all the way down
to the bottom of my shoes.

1709
01:19:21,280 --> 01:19:22,475
Rose, I...

1710
01:19:24,880 --> 01:19:27,679
I can't give that up.

1711
01:19:33,480 --> 01:19:35,631
Well, maybe you ought to go on
and stay down there with her,

1712
01:19:35,720 --> 01:19:37,393
if she's a better woman than me.

1713
01:19:37,480 --> 01:19:39,233
It ain't about nobody being
a better woman, or nothing.

1714
01:19:39,320 --> 01:19:40,640
Rose, you ain't to blame.

1715
01:19:40,720 --> 01:19:42,996
A man couldn't ask
for a better wife than you've been.

1716
01:19:43,080 --> 01:19:44,560
I'm responsible for it.

1717
01:19:44,640 --> 01:19:46,199
I done locked myself into a pattern,

1718
01:19:46,280 --> 01:19:48,272
trying to take care of you all,
that I forgot about myself.

1719
01:19:48,360 --> 01:19:49,999
Well, what the hell was I there for?

1720
01:19:50,080 --> 01:19:51,639
That was my job, not somebody else's.

1721
01:19:51,720 --> 01:19:54,838
Rose, listen to me.
I done tried all my life to live decent.

1722
01:19:54,920 --> 01:19:57,833
To live a clean, hard, useful life.

1723
01:19:57,920 --> 01:20:01,072
I try to be a good husband to you,
in every way I know how.

1724
01:20:01,160 --> 01:20:03,356
Maybe I come into the world backwards,
I don't know,

1725
01:20:03,440 --> 01:20:06,751
but you're born with two strikes on you
before you come to the plate.

1726
01:20:06,840 --> 01:20:07,956
You got to guard it closely,

1727
01:20:08,040 --> 01:20:10,680
always looking for the curveball
on the inside corner.

1728
01:20:10,760 --> 01:20:12,399
You can't afford a called strike.

1729
01:20:12,480 --> 01:20:13,834
You can't let nothing get past you.

1730
01:20:13,920 --> 01:20:16,037
If you're going down,
you're doing down swinging.

1731
01:20:16,120 --> 01:20:18,840
Everything lined up against you!

1732
01:20:20,520 --> 01:20:22,034
What you gonna do?

1733
01:20:23,640 --> 01:20:26,075
I fooled them, Rose. I bunted.

1734
01:20:26,520 --> 01:20:30,355
When I found you and Cory
and a halfway decent job, I was safe.

1735
01:20:30,440 --> 01:20:32,636
Couldn't nothing touch me!

1736
01:20:32,720 --> 01:20:34,154
I wasn't gonna strike out no more.

1737
01:20:34,240 --> 01:20:35,640
I wasn't going back to the penitentiary.

1738
01:20:35,720 --> 01:20:38,076
I wasn't gonna lie in the street
with a bottle of wine.

1739
01:20:38,160 --> 01:20:42,439
I was safe. I had me a family, a job.

1740
01:20:43,640 --> 01:20:46,314
I wasn't gonna get that last strike.

1741
01:20:48,080 --> 01:20:50,959
I was standing on first base,

1742
01:20:51,040 --> 01:20:52,997
waiting for one of them boys
to knock me in, to bring me home.

1743
01:20:53,080 --> 01:20:54,878
You should have stayed in my bed, Troy.

1744
01:20:54,960 --> 01:20:56,394
Then I saw the gal,
she firmed up my backbone.

1745
01:20:56,480 --> 01:20:59,439
I got to thinkin' that if I tried,
maybe I could steal second.

1746
01:20:59,520 --> 01:21:01,000
- You understand?
- You should've held me tight.

1747
01:21:01,080 --> 01:21:04,471
- You should've grabbed me and held on.
- I stood on first base for 18 years,

1748
01:21:04,560 --> 01:21:06,950
and I thought, well,
God damn it, go on for it!

1749
01:21:07,040 --> 01:21:09,430
We ain't talking about baseball!

1750
01:21:09,520 --> 01:21:11,830
We talking about you going off
and laying up with another woman,

1751
01:21:11,920 --> 01:21:12,910
then bringing it home to me.

1752
01:21:13,000 --> 01:21:15,276
That's what we're talking about.
We're not talkin' about no baseball!

1753
01:21:15,360 --> 01:21:16,510
Rose, you're not listening to me.

1754
01:21:16,640 --> 01:21:19,519
I'm trying to explain it to you
the best way I know how.

1755
01:21:21,080 --> 01:21:25,552
It's not easy for me to admit that I've been
standing in the same place for 18 years!

1756
01:21:25,640 --> 01:21:28,155
Well, I've been standing with you!

1757
01:21:28,240 --> 01:21:32,280
I've been right here with you, Troy!
I got a life, too.

1758
01:21:32,360 --> 01:21:36,593
I gave 18 years of my life
to stand in the same spot as you!

1759
01:21:36,680 --> 01:21:38,637
Don't you think
I ever wanted other things?

1760
01:21:38,720 --> 01:21:40,837
Don't you think I had dreams and hopes?

1761
01:21:40,920 --> 01:21:43,515
What about my life? What about me?

1762
01:21:43,600 --> 01:21:46,190
Don't you think it ever crossed my
mind to want to know other men?

1763
01:21:46,280 --> 01:21:50,593
That I wanted to lay up somewhere
and forget about my responsibilities?

1764
01:21:50,680 --> 01:21:52,273
That I wanted someone to make me laugh,

1765
01:21:52,360 --> 01:21:54,397
so I could feel good?

1766
01:21:54,480 --> 01:21:56,551
You're not the only one
who's got wants and needs.

1767
01:21:56,680 --> 01:21:58,592
But I held on to you, Troy.

1768
01:21:58,680 --> 01:22:02,833
I took all my feelings,
my wants and needs and dreams,

1769
01:22:02,920 --> 01:22:04,718
and I buried them inside you.

1770
01:22:04,800 --> 01:22:07,076
I planted a seed
and watched and prayed over it.

1771
01:22:07,160 --> 01:22:10,153
I planted myself inside you
and waited to bloom!

1772
01:22:10,240 --> 01:22:14,075
And it didn't take me no 18 years
to realize the soil was hard and rocky,

1773
01:22:14,160 --> 01:22:16,277
and it wasn't never gonna bloom!

1774
01:22:16,360 --> 01:22:19,273
But I held on to you, Troy.
I held you tighter.

1775
01:22:19,360 --> 01:22:21,352
You was my husband.

1776
01:22:21,440 --> 01:22:24,080
I owed you everything I had.

1777
01:22:24,160 --> 01:22:26,834
Every part of me I could find to give you.

1778
01:22:26,960 --> 01:22:30,749
And upstairs in that bedroom,
with the darkness falling in on me,

1779
01:22:30,880 --> 01:22:34,954
I gave everything I had
to try and erase the doubt

1780
01:22:35,040 --> 01:22:37,714
that you wasn't the finest man
in the world.

1781
01:22:37,800 --> 01:22:40,474
And wherever you was going,
I was gonna be there with you,

1782
01:22:40,600 --> 01:22:43,035
because you was my husband.

1783
01:22:44,480 --> 01:22:47,473
'Cause that's the only way
I was gonna survive as your wife.

1784
01:22:48,720 --> 01:22:52,396
You always talking about what you give
and what you don't have to give.

1785
01:22:53,080 --> 01:22:54,799
But you take, too, Troy.

1786
01:22:54,880 --> 01:22:57,520
You take and
don't even know nobody's giving.

1787
01:22:57,600 --> 01:22:58,590
You say I take and don't give.

1788
01:22:58,680 --> 01:22:59,830
Troy, you're hurting me.

1789
01:22:59,920 --> 01:23:01,832
- Troy, you're hurting my arm, let go!
- I gave you everything I got.

1790
01:23:01,920 --> 01:23:03,195
Don't you tell that lie on me.

1791
01:23:03,280 --> 01:23:04,680
- Mama!
- Don't you tell that lie!

1792
01:23:04,760 --> 01:23:06,274
Troy, you're hurting me!

1793
01:23:06,880 --> 01:23:08,234
Troy! Troy!

1794
01:23:08,640 --> 01:23:12,316
All right. That's strike two.

1795
01:23:13,160 --> 01:23:17,359
You stay away from around me, boy.
Don't you strike out.

1796
01:23:19,040 --> 01:23:21,032
You're living with a full count.

1797
01:23:24,600 --> 01:23:26,398
Don't you strike out!

1798
01:26:46,880 --> 01:26:48,712
Troy, I want to talk to you.

1799
01:26:51,360 --> 01:26:53,431
All of a sudden?

1800
01:26:55,480 --> 01:26:57,949
After all this time,
you want to talk to me, huh?

1801
01:26:59,040 --> 01:27:00,520
You ain't wanted to talk to me in months.

1802
01:27:00,600 --> 01:27:01,920
You ain't wanted to talk to me last night.

1803
01:27:02,000 --> 01:27:03,480
You didn't want no parts of me then.

1804
01:27:04,120 --> 01:27:06,112
What you want to talk to me about now?

1805
01:27:09,760 --> 01:27:12,719
- Tomorrow's Friday.
- I know what day tomorrow is.

1806
01:27:12,800 --> 01:27:13,950
You think I don't know tomorrow's Friday?

1807
01:27:14,080 --> 01:27:16,231
My whole life, I ain't done nothing
but look to see Friday coming,

1808
01:27:16,320 --> 01:27:17,640
and you got to tell me it's Friday.

1809
01:27:17,720 --> 01:27:19,234
I want to know if you're coming home.

1810
01:27:19,800 --> 01:27:22,235
I always come home, Rose. You know that.

1811
01:27:22,320 --> 01:27:23,674
Ain't never been a night
I ain't come home.

1812
01:27:23,800 --> 01:27:25,439
That ain't what I mean, and you know it.

1813
01:27:25,640 --> 01:27:29,077
I wanna know if you're coming
straight home after work.

1814
01:27:29,160 --> 01:27:32,119
I figured I'd cash my check,
hang out at Taylors' with the boys.

1815
01:27:32,200 --> 01:27:33,316
Maybe play a game of checkers.

1816
01:27:33,400 --> 01:27:35,995
Troy, I can't live like this.
I won't live like this.

1817
01:27:36,080 --> 01:27:37,480
You're living on borrowed time with me.

1818
01:27:37,560 --> 01:27:39,552
Been going on six months now,
you ain't been coming home.

1819
01:27:39,640 --> 01:27:41,677
I come home every night.
Every night of the year.

1820
01:27:41,760 --> 01:27:44,229
That's 365 days.

1821
01:27:45,760 --> 01:27:48,355
I want you to come home
tomorrow after work.

1822
01:27:53,360 --> 01:27:57,036
Rose, I don't mess up my pay.
You know that.

1823
01:27:57,120 --> 01:27:58,998
I take my pay, I give it to you.

1824
01:27:59,080 --> 01:28:02,437
I don't have no money
but what you give me back.

1825
01:28:02,520 --> 01:28:05,672
I just want a little time to myself.

1826
01:28:05,800 --> 01:28:06,950
A little time to enjoy life.

1827
01:28:07,040 --> 01:28:08,918
What about me?
When's my time to enjoy life?

1828
01:28:09,000 --> 01:28:11,071
I don't know what to tell you, Rose.
I'm doing the best I can.

1829
01:28:11,160 --> 01:28:12,196
You ain't been comin' home from work,

1830
01:28:12,280 --> 01:28:13,634
but time enough
to change your clothes and run out.

1831
01:28:13,720 --> 01:28:15,712
You wanna call that the best you can do?

1832
01:28:17,280 --> 01:28:20,352
I'm going over to the hospital
to see Alberta.

1833
01:28:21,480 --> 01:28:23,153
She went into the hospital this afternoon.

1834
01:28:23,240 --> 01:28:26,677
Looks like she might have the baby early.

1835
01:28:27,560 --> 01:28:29,233
I won't be gone long.

1836
01:28:35,640 --> 01:28:38,709
Well, you ought to know. They went over
to Miss Pearl's and got Gabe today.

1837
01:28:38,800 --> 01:28:42,555
She said you told them to
go ahead and lock him up.

1838
01:28:42,640 --> 01:28:46,600
I ain't said no such thing.
Whoever told you that is telling a lie.

1839
01:28:46,680 --> 01:28:48,399
Miss Pearl ain't doing nothing
but telling a big, fat lie.

1840
01:28:48,480 --> 01:28:50,358
She ain't had to tell me.
I read it on the papers.

1841
01:28:50,440 --> 01:28:52,557
- What'd it say, huh?
- It said you told them to take him.

1842
01:28:52,680 --> 01:28:54,831
Then they screwed that up,
just like they screw up everything.

1843
01:28:54,920 --> 01:28:56,149
I ain't worried about
what they got on that paper.

1844
01:28:56,240 --> 01:28:58,152
It say the government sends
part of the check to the hospital,

1845
01:28:58,240 --> 01:28:59,310
the other part to you.

1846
01:28:59,400 --> 01:29:01,039
I got nothing to do with that,
if that's the way it works.

1847
01:29:01,120 --> 01:29:02,236
I don't make up the rules...

1848
01:29:02,320 --> 01:29:03,595
You did Gabe just like you did Cory.

1849
01:29:03,680 --> 01:29:04,875
You wouldn't sign the paper for Cory,

1850
01:29:04,960 --> 01:29:06,599
but you signed for Gabe!
You signed that paper!

1851
01:29:06,680 --> 01:29:08,512
I told you I ain't signed nothing, woman.

1852
01:29:08,600 --> 01:29:10,159
Hell, the only thing I signed
was the release form.

1853
01:29:10,280 --> 01:29:11,270
Hell, I can't read,

1854
01:29:11,360 --> 01:29:12,680
I don't know what they had on that paper.

1855
01:29:12,760 --> 01:29:14,592
I ain't signed nothing
about sending Gabe away.

1856
01:29:14,680 --> 01:29:16,831
I said send him to the hospital,
you said let him go free.

1857
01:29:16,920 --> 01:29:17,910
Then you went down there

1858
01:29:18,040 --> 01:29:19,474
and you signed him to the hospital
for half his money.

1859
01:29:19,560 --> 01:29:21,836
You went back on yourself, Troy.
You're gonna have to answer for that.

1860
01:29:21,960 --> 01:29:23,519
You just been over there
talking to Miss Pearl.

1861
01:29:23,600 --> 01:29:26,160
She just mad 'cause she ain't gettin'
Gabe's rent money, that's all it is.

1862
01:29:26,240 --> 01:29:27,674
